issue.title: Bug fixes and common API unifications
issue.body:
1- converted randomness initialization to unseeded np.random.RandomState(), this will force the random number generator to take from /dev/urandom on linux (or from its equivalent on other systems) and achieve strong randomness.
2- converted the random number generator to a stream object, as a best practice for future expansion where multiple randomness objects with different random states are needed.
3- moved the teleportation example to its own directory to declutter the workspace.
4- converted the teleportation example to a bottlepy base, as the flask example wasn't running successfully, then added a usage doc-string for the user.
5- unified the examples' imports to "import kite as kt", then used "kt.<some_function/class>" as a common method of usage.
6- unified the library's import from explicit relative imports to Absolute imports for better readability, e.g. "from kite.<module> import <class>"
